==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: onshore
<hw>onshore</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>coming from the sea toward the
land; -- of winds and weather; <as>as, an <ex>onshore</ex> gale</as>.
Opposed to <ant>offshore</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> inshore, seaward.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>On the edge of the land; near the shoreline; <as>as,
an <ex>onshore</ex> lighthouse</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>onside</ent>⟦br⟧
